tle = 10. Still 10 total.\n\nOr maybe the tool counts title differently and gets 10+1=11? Unclear.\n\nGiven that the knowledge file has 10 sections and I count 10 headings in the source (including title), and the source structure maps well to the knowledge sections, I think the automated warning is a false positive. I should not report this as a finding since the counts actually match.\n\nNow I'm checking whether \"リテラル値\" should appear in the hints for s8. It's listed as a converter name in the source, and since it appears as a first column value in the table, it likely qualifies under V4's requirements for property names. The class name `nablarch.core.dataformat.convertor.value.DefaultValue` is already in the hints, but the converter name itself might be missing—this could be a minor gap worth noting. Looking at the section count more carefully, the knowledge file has 10 sections total (s1 for the title, s2-s10 for the nine h2 headings), which matches the source structure perfectly, so the automated warning about 11 sections appears to be incorrect and I won't include it as a finding. For V1, I'm verifying the image reference in s10 matches the source file correctly. So far the only real issue I've found is the missing \"リテラル値\" converter name in V4's s8 hints.\n\nNow I'm checking V1's introductory sections for any content gaps. The source includes navigation references to other Nablarch documentation in s1, s9, and s10, but the knowledge file appropriately omits these since they're just pointers to external resources rather than actual implementation details.\n\nLooking at s3 more carefully, I notice the hints are incomplete. The source lists three packages—`please.change.me.core.dataformat`, `please.change.me.core.dataformat.convertor`, and `please.change.me.test.core.file`—but the hints only capture the first one along with \"FormUrlEncoded\" and \"コアパッケージ\". The missing package names should be included in the hints since they're property names directly from the section content.\n\nI'm also spotting a second issue with s8: the hint \"リテラル値\" is missing, which appears as the first column converter name in the field converter table.\n\nSo I have two minor V4 findings to report: s3 is missing hints for those two package names, and s8 is missing the literal value hint.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":18944,"cache_read_input_tokens":35069,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":18944,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5f5194a4-276f-4a49-b5b0-e936244d8440","uuid":"a86e734a-e17d-4f5b-9d6a-b32ee7c26d0a"}
